name: Rayyann Cafe
description: A highly-rated cafe celebrated for its aesthetic, comfortable ambiance and delicious coffee, especially the cappuccino. It's a popular spot for socializing, studying, or simply relaxing.
brief_description: Aesthetic cafe, cozy ambiance, delicious coffee, great value.
review_entities:
Rekomended!!! Tempatnya bersih!! Cappuccino nya rekomen ğŸ‘ğŸ»||Tempat paling recomendasi buat nyantai, ngerjain tugas, meeting dll.

Menu di ala carte juga gak mahal, enak enak ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ â€¦||Full 5 bintang. ğŸŒŸğŸŒŸğŸŒŸğŸŒŸğŸŒŸ
Sampai detik ini sih masih bintang 5 ya meski ada kekurangannya, tapi masih oke banget untuk sekitaran Bungah.

Buka dari jam 11.00 sampai jam 22.00

Tempatnya meski di lantai 2, tapi cozy dan instagramable.
Ada outdoor dan indoor.
Indoornya ada AC. Meskipun 4 AC tapi Ndak begitu dingin.
Sepertinya ada live music tapi g tau kapan.
Ada musholla dan satu toilet, bersih kok.
Yang penting saling jaga ya gaes..

Menu.
Menunya variatif dan harganya masih masuk akal kantong kok.
Mulai dari nasi, mie, dimsum, sampai pukis kekinian alias pancong.
Minumannya juga banyak varian. Coklatnya enak.
Sayangnya beberapa kali kesana ice creamnya sama gyoza belum ready juga. Jadi g bisa ngesunday deh..
Tapi it's okay, masih enak kok disana.

Cara pesannya, menu bisa dibawa ke meja untuk dilihat2 dulu lalu pesan dan langsung bayar ke meja order. Lali tunggu sampai nama kamu dipanggil. Kamu duduk manis sambil lambaikan tangan aja cz hidangan kamu akan diantar ke mejamu.
Ah pokoknya pelayanannya oke deh..
Cepat juga kok.

Saranku buat kalian, jangan lupa bawa tissue ya.. cz disana tidak menyediakan Tissue.

Semoga bertahan tetap bisa memberikan yang terbaik ya..  tempat baru yg cukup recommended lah buat ngumpul ataupun nugas.||Tempatnya bersih, dan nyaman. name: Wang Yu
description: Medan's pioneer Sichuan mala spot, featuring authentic spicy fish dishes. Offers a spacious, modern oriental ambiance with well-presented, sophisticated food. Highly rated and good value.

2. Saute Cauliflower. Masi okay lumayan enak tetapi agak oilyy ya.

Simple food but 5-star taste.||love this original taste from china culture. i like to recomend the greenpepper spicy fish, Baby mala lobster, lima rasa bumbu ayam, Telur Tomat .||NICE PLACE TO ENJOY DINNER

Kami datang di hari MINGGU, hanya terisi 60%. Mungkin terdengar mouth to mouth soal harga ikan nya.

Atmosfir suasana, lighting, interior dan furniture top notch. Cocok untuk makan bersama keluarga maupun membawa tamu.

Sesuai merek nya Wang Yu, yang artinya Raja Ikan, tentu specialty ikan. Untuk grapu dengan harga 499 ribu, sedikit banyak membuat orang tidak masuk.

GREEN PEPPER GRILLED FISH
Kami pesan Ikan Panggang Lada HIJAU dengan harapan tidak membuat mulut jadi kebas oleh merica mala. Kami tidak mau pesan Spicy Grilled Fish karena ini full cabe mala. Walaupun hanya Lada Hijau ( chin chiau), bau cabe khas Sichuan itu tetap terasa. Saya kurang suka.

Penampilan piring yang dipakai memukau. Ikan saat dibawa ke meja dalam keadaan belum dipanaskan. Jadi harus tunggu sebentar hingga kuah nya mendidih. Ikan nya sendiri menurut saya sedikit overcooked. Saya tanya waiter api nya apakah bisa dimatikan, katanya sudah dengan timer dan akan padam sendiri.

TELUR TOMAT ( scrambled egg with tomatoes).
Ini khas masakan dari china. Walau terlihat simple, memerlukan keahlian agar enak. Dan telur tomat Wang Yu, best of the best. Medan belum ada yang seenak ini. Saus nya sweet dan harum. Scrambled egg nya, bagian kulit nya luar biasa wangi.

STEAMED EGG WITH MINCED MEAT
Telur kukus daging cincang. Dish ini bukan best of the best. Steamed egg bukan terlembut yang pernah saya makan. Minced meat nya perlu lebih wangi, kurang nendang. Kalau boleh usul, sebaiknya penampakan nya harus seperti gambar di menu yakni 1/2 egg + 1/2 meat. Yang keluar tadi semua tertutup meat.

Overall dinner malam di Wang Yu oke. Kalau datang lagi akan minta ikan nya cukup di grill bentar saja serta akan mencoba dish lain yang non mala.

Grading system :
FOOD :
5 = Delicious & Tantalizing
4 = Above Average
3 = Just OK
2 = Bad

SERVICE :
5 = Excellent Service from  Entering till Leaving.
4 = Good Service
3 = Just OK
2 = Under

ATMOSPHERE
5 = Positive Vibe
4 = Feel OK
3 = So so
2 = Feel Uncomfortable||A newly opened non-halal Chinese restaurant in Medan specialised Hunan dishes especially fish.

Ordered its braised pork belly with broccoli and potato, stir fried bean sprouts with chives.||The food are awesome. The green pepper fish taste even better than T**Yu. Other than fish, they also serve a lot of varieties of dishes like chicken, pork and beef.

Very nice interior, and I will definitely come back again soon.||Mewah tempatnya

brief_description: Legendary noodles, generous portions, delicious chili oil.
review_entities:
Love this place for cheap local food.||Walau suasana agak jadul, tapi rasa masakan nya enak, saya pesan Nasi Goreng Bebek dan Rujak Juhi. Suasananya cukup nyaman dan penerangan tidak terlalu terang. Kadang ada promo Gopay.||Restoran legend yang sudah mulai dimakan jaman.
Jaman saya kecil, orang tua saya suka sekali makan di Bakmi Gang Kelinci, jaman dimana Bakmi GM rasa nya belum ada dan Bakmi Gang Kelinci masih belum banyak cabangnya seperti sekarang.

Namun waktu berlalu, siapa yang berubah mengikuti jaman pasti akan bertahan, semoga Bakmi GK juga bisa bertahan di tengah persaingan F&B yang begitu ketat.

Untuk mienya 11-12 dengan Bakmi GM, namun kecepatan pelayanan perlu ditingkatkan, kecepatan penyajian juga perlu ditingkatkan, interior juga perlu ditingkatkan mengikuti perkembangan jaman agar bisa "instgramable" Kalo kata anak anak sekarang, jadi kesannya nggak dingin kalau dilihat dari luar.

Untuk anak-anak jaman sekarang kadang tampilan makanan dan tempat lebih penting dari rasa makanan itu sendiri â˜ºğŸ™||Sebelum dateng kesini coba liat2 reviewnya dulu, lumayan banyak yg kasih bintang 1. Terletak di selatan klinik As-Syifa barat jalan, dengan spot menghadap ke timur. Tempat ini merupakan sebuah Depot (pagi - Siang hari) dan Cafe (Sore hari).

Cafe ini memiliki desain yang minimalis dengan finishing yang bagus sehingga enak untuk dipandang dan nyaman untuk dikunjungi.

Cafe ini memiliki tiga area tempat duduk dimana diantaranya adalah, kursi dan meja, lesehan dan kursi tinggi.

Menu yang disediakan cukup beragam mulai dari minuman kekinian, kopi kopian dan aneka snack untuk menemani cangkrukan kita.

Untuk Laksa Mee baru pertama icip nih, enak. Dalemnya banyak ada bakso ikan, tahu, dll. Rasanya gurih, dan asinnya juga pas. Paling mantep lagi kalo pake sambel dan jeruk nipisnya.

Aku cobain yang cabang Chillax karena emang ada urusan meeting bareng rekan mampir deh kesini buat lunch. Harganya affordable, lokasinya gak perlu diragukan lagi. Udah pasti banyak spot Instagramable, spot sunset dan pastinya worth it banget buat Dine in disini. Take away juga ok dan gak ngurangin kualitas dari makanan tersebut.

Aku cobain beberapa variannya. Ada laksa seafood, kaya butter toast, kwetiaw seafood, kari ayam, jus kedondong, kopi tarik, iced teh tarik, barley. Worth to buy!

 'Bar ini letaknya cukup tersembunyi - terletak di lantai 4 dan 5 sebuah ruko pertokoan di sebelah komplek Tribrata Dharmawangsa. Lokasinya sangat strategis. Dapat diakses dengan mudah menggunakan transportasi publik (MRT).\n\nBarnya sendiri kapasitasnya cukup kecil, tapi terdiri dari dua lantai. Yang di lantai 4 yang indoor dan lantai 5 outdoor (di rooftop bangunan). Hari-hari biasa, pelayanan hanya dilakukan di lantai 4 saja. Tapi jika ada event, pelayanan bisa dilakukan ke lantai 5 (kalau gak ada event, kita bisa tetep ke lantai 5 tapi self-service ngambil makan/minum sendiri ke bawah).\n\nDi hari biasa dan minggu malam, sepi banget! Seru buat tempat kalau mau ngobrol sama circle yang intimate. Diiringi lagu-lagu pop Jepang dan anime, obrolan bisa jadi tambah seru. Sembari menikmati berbagai snack dan makanan khas Jepang yang cukup lezat (yakitorinya enak-enak!). Cocktailnya pun enak-enak (you know what I mean). Kalau tidak salah yg cukup greng adalah yang namanya "tsunami", sebuah cocktail berwarna biru.'
 'Ke sini karena lihat review bintang 5 di google. Namunâ€¦ untuk tempat yang harus naik tangga 4 lantai, I expect makanannya sepadan dengan usaha ke tempat ini. Sayangnya ini ngga terjadi. Too bad. Sama sekali ngga expect yakitori bisa sekurang ini rasanya. Mungkin karena digoreng, jadi kerasğŸ¥¹ Sungguh ngga sepadan sama harganya yang lumayan pricey. Ide bikin tempat hidden gini menarik sebenernya, tapi please makanannya dibikin sepadan kualitasnya, biar dapet juga â€œgemâ€-nya ğŸ«¥ğŸ«¥ğŸ«¥'
 "Small bar with great ambiance and good food. Sometimes they have karaoke night together with fun people and patrons. Small problem, we need to take stairs to 3rd floor. Mindful when you drink, you might can't go down safely (lol)"
 'koktelnya enak banget aseli!!!'
 'Great drinks and cozy. Always a blast to hang around here with friends!!']

name: PUKU Bali
description: A highly-rated ramen spot, famed for its homemade noodles, delicious pork buns, and crispy char siu. Enjoy a quiet atmosphere with beautiful rice field views. A must-visit.
brief_description: Homemade ramen, pork buns, rice field views.
review_entities:
Had a decent pork Tonkotsu ramen at PUKU.  The broth was creamy and rich in flavor. Although not exactly as flavorful and balanced like a typical Japanese Ramen broth. I would call it a bit rough around the edges.
The noodles were a bit on the overcooked side and their texture a bit course, not silky yet with a bite as I normally like them.  But given that this place is in rural Indonesia and not Japan, it will pass as a decent 4 out of 5 Ramen. In Tokyo it would give it 3 out of 5 stars.

The restaurant setting is simple but acceptable, there are some tables that overlook a rice paddy, although we were there for dinner and couldnâ€™t see much due to the darkness.||Very tasty food, and friendly staff. Highest recommendation.||Well worth the visit. I had the miso soup but could not taste the miso. Then I had the smoked chicken soup, small but nice. The pork buns were delicious. Quiet place. I just wish there was no smoking. Noodles are fresh homemade.||Small place but delicious food. They also sell frozen food||Our favorite neighborhood place! Delicious food and friendly owners ğŸ’š â€¦||We went in without planning, because the place looked nice and had good reviews. I can say the reviews were right! The ramen was very good, and the appetizers were tasty too. Everything came quickly and the service was great. Nice food and a cool atmosphere!||Never thought Iâ€™d enjoy eating Japanese style ramen in Bali. Apparently, the chef/owner studied in Japan so no wonder it tasted really good.  Everything that we ordered tasted delicious and the service was friendly and attentive.  Cool little space. They also have a gelato||What a hidden gem! Iâ€™m surprised isnâ€™t more popular. Best dumplings in Ubud. The gyozas and buns also fantastic. But the rice bowls oh my god heaven on earth. Keep up the good work.||Everything was amazing, the owner was friendly and wonderful, he helped us with our bikes. The noodles and dumplings was freshly hand made, the crackling pork is crispy and had some beautiful flavours. To top it off we got two free gelato ice cream per couple for spending 400k total which tasted great.||The ham sandwich is really good!||Very good food. I ordered steamed bun with pork which turned out very very yummy and flavorful. Ramen is sooo close to authentic flavor in Japan. And crispy roasted pork with tender juicy meat and airy bubbly skin outside which is good too.

Great combination of Chinese and Japanese cuisine in one place||We had been looking for good ramen in Bali and found it here in Ubud. After seeing the great ratings, we decided to come, and it was definitely the best decision. The food is amazing, the ramen is delicious, the buns are excellent, the view of the rice field is beautiful, and the music fits perfectly. Add a tasty ginger beer to that, and wow. We will gladly come back.||Ordered a chicken ramen, light broth, easy to eat.||Very delicious, simple and very easy to prepare. Puku pork ramen and smoked pork ham are highly recommended to try. Will definitely repeat order. Love it so much||I have tried all of their smoked meat selections, but I'm definitely hooked with their smoked chicken. It's not as spicy as the smoked pork ones though. But that's not a big deal since I can just use my own spices to add to its flavor, which is fun to do.||The best ramen and noodles in town, additional wonton soup for rainy and cold weather will warm you up||I love this place so much! then foods are good, especially the gyoza, will definitely come visit again. and i love kako as my bsf!||By far the best place for ramen, pork rice and pork bao!!! ğŸ’¯ authentic and value for money. Iâ€™m in love ğŸ˜||First time trying crispy pork, and it was amazing! Best dumplings and ramen Iâ€™ve ever had :)||One of the best Ramen places in Ubud. They make all their noodles. Broth is great.  Everything is good and the staff are nice.

Thankyou!!||Good food, nice bartenders...ğŸ˜ƒğŸ‘ğŸ»||Rawon dan teh lychee nya top||Saya selalu mencari kafe untuk sekedar santai membaca buku atau hanya menikmati suasananya ditemani hidangan kue dan minuman. Namun biasanya kafe seperti ini punya masalah berikut:
1. Harga kuenya sangat mahal
2. Kuenya terlalu lembut (kebanyakan soda kue) atau terlalu banyak krim atau terlalu manis
3. Minumannya disediakan menggunakan gelas plastik dan volume airnya lebih sedikit daripada es batunya
4. Musiknya terlalu keras
5. Tidak ada stop kontak untuk pelanggan

Sewaktu saya mampir ke kafe ini secara tidak sengaja, karena awalnya berniat mengantar ibu ke klinik di sebelahnya, tidak ada ekspektasi apapun melainkan hanya ingin bekerja di kafe. Waktu itu, tahun 2024, tersedia promo paket kue + minuman seharga Rp 45k (tahun ini 2025 jadi Rp 48k). Menariknya, saya bebas memilih kue apapun dan minuman apapun. Saya memilih kue cokelat dan minuman chocolate latte (bukan seperti di foto).

Saat pesanan diantar, saya tidak menyangka diberikan potongan kue berbentuk segitiga, bukan potongan balok tipis seperti brownis pada umumnya. Padahal ukuran itu biasanya dihargai lebih mahal. Kue ini disajikan di piring kecil dan sendok kecil (mirip seperti di foto). Waktu saya potong dengan sendok, teksturnya cukup padat seperti gelato yang masih dingin. Saat saya coba, rasa cokelatnya lebih kuat daripada gulanya. Tidak terlalu manis namun imbang dengan cokelatnya. Bukan seperti perisa cokelat yang terlalu manis. Ibu saya ikut mengincipi dan suka dengan kuenya. Padahal beliau selalu menghindari kue karena rasanya cenderung manis.

Minuman chocolate latte-nya juga disediakan dengan gelas kaca (mirip seperti di foto) dan airnya lebih banyak daripada es batunya. Soal rasa, bisa jadi karena saya sudah menyantap kue cokelat, rasa minuman cokelatnya tidak begitu manis namun tidak juga tawar.

Selama bekerja disini, saya tidak perlu khawatir untuk kehabisan baterai karena tersedia stop kontak, meski tidak banyak. Musik di kafe juga terdengar lirih memainkan nada piano jazz. Pengunjung juga tidak banyak di siang hari.

Mei 2025 saya menyempatkan lagi untuk mampir kedua kalinya dan menuliskan ulasan ini. Seperti foto yang saya cantumkan, saya memesan Cheese Cake dan Baileys Caffe (non-alcohol). Sebenarnya saya ingin mencoba Red Velvet namun tidak tersedia saat itu. Promo kue+minuman masih berlaku namun harganya Rp 48k, tahun baru harga baru. Tekstur kuenya tetap padat dan rasa kejunya lebih terasa daripada gulanya. Bisa dibilang ketika di lidah, rasanya berubah seiring waktu. Berawal dari rasa keju, kemudian ketika sudah ditelan, perlahan di lidah akan muncul rasa manis. Bila kita makan kuenya terus menerus atau dalam jumlah banyak, rasa manisnya akan semakin kuat di lidah. Mungkin ini kenapa ada yang berkomentar rasa kuenya terlalu manis. Saya sendiri menikmati kuenya hanya 1 sendok kecil per 10 halaman buku.

Minuman dan makanan juga menjadi faktor "terlalu manis". Baileys Caffe cenderung pahit, rasa manisnya hanya sedikit. Saya tidak bisa banyak berkomentar yang asli bagaimana karena hanya penasaran untuk mencoba. Suasana di kafe masih sama, siang hari masih sepi dan suara piano jazz memecah sunyi dengan irama yang tak tentu.

Bila ingin bersantai di kafe sambil menyantap kue dan minuman dengan harga tidak begitu mahal, saya rekomendasikan mampir ke kafe Serundai. Kafe ini juga menyediakan makanan berat namun saya belum pernah mencobanya. Semoga kafe ini bisa menjadi salah satu favorit anda juga.||Beh beh beh Rawon e wenak tenan...jan jan...cuoooocokkk tenan....Pro tips, pesen o krupuk maneh, kurang soale .||Makanannya enak tapi sayang pelayanannya lama.||Makanan dan minuman lumayan enak disini, blm coba cake nya infonya enak next kalau kesini lagi mau coba, ruang ber-AC, yang bisa smoking cuman dikit d lantai 2 kayaknya..

brief_description: Beach club, sunset views, grilled fish, seafood pasta.
review_entities:
nice place for hanging out and spend some time, especially before flying home.

name: The Mailroom
description: A unique speakeasy bar in Canggu, requiring a key hunt for entry. Features a vibrant atmosphere with live music and creative cocktails. Highly recommended is the 'Lord of Himself', a smoky whiskey-based drink.
brief_description: Unique speakeasy bar, find the key, enjoy creative cocktails.
review_entities:
Unfortunately my photos don't do them justice but the drinks here are incredibly unique. They have a wide array of options for anyone looking for sweet, gentle drinks to getting completely blasted.   Take your time and enjoy the menu. The illustrations and drink presentations are incredible.

The staff are fantastic as well! Daisy was my waitress and I really enjoyed chatting with her. I also burned through four servings of the free chips and she said nothing except to bring me more.

I went on a Friday night around midnight and there was a lot of seating, so please don't let not having a reservation deter you and just show up. On Monday nights around 10pm is when they have the magician.

If you're having trouble finding them, look for the place on the corner with a simple black sign with a key on it. It's next to Mesa, on the right.||Fanciest cocktail presentations in this speakeasy bar! Recommend||A small, lovely hidden bar in Bali that everyone should visit during your time in Bali. Their drinks are amazing and they put a lot of effort in presenting them as well.

Shoutout to the bartender Kadek, who made us a drink based on our request for sweet coconut and pandan flavour. It turns out being one of the best drink we ever had.

Will definitely visit this spot again.||A hidden gem dor cocktail lovers!! From the moment i walked in, the vibe was perfect!! Moody Lighting, chill music and the bartender team that clearly knows their craft! The cocktail menu is very very unique.||A fun speakeasy in Berawa, Canggu. They take reservations on WhatsApp and give you your mailbox number through a response message. When locating the bar, look for the low, green-light illuminated key signpost between Gelato Secrets and Fineline jewelry store. You will be let into a small mailroom where you retrieve your key from your numbered box and open the door to the bar.

The bar is dimly lit, semi-romantic or club-y, and they sometimes have live DJs. They have an inventive and fun menu that includes a drink that is poured via a miniature custom IV bag. They also have a drink that comes in a miniature bathtub. The bartenders are knowledgeable and made me some cool custom drinks like a mezcal espresso martini and a tequila drink that used cucumber and spiced salt, but tasted almost like a watermelon Jolly Rancher.

Itâ€™s slightly pricey, but itâ€™s a unique and fun experience thatâ€™s worth trying out whether youâ€™re with friends, on a date, or just traveling solo. Itâ€™s definitely one of the more interesting bars in the greater Canggu area. Thanks, guys!||This place is AMAZING! I almost couldnâ€™t find it, which in my opinion makes a really great speakeasy! Fun entry where you have to find the right mailbox containing a key to let you in. Once inside, the experience just got even better! INCREDIBLE bartenders (shout out to Adi!) who can make up fantastic, delicious drinks based on your preferences. The menu is filled with creative cocktails, all served with a fun presentation (my favorite!) Sip on some show stopping drinks, eat some of the tasty complimentary snacks, and take a picture in the very instagramable bathroom! Ohâ€”and there was a MAGICIAN?! So good!!! I literally canâ€™t stop talking about how much I loved this place!||I had a great time at The Mailroom! I went alone and felt welcomed right away. The bartender and the entire bar team were incredibly friendly, creating a relaxed and enjoyable atmosphere. The drinks were both creative and delicious, making it a perfect spot for anyone looking for something unique and tasty. I highly recommend it.||We had a great Time! The Staff was really friendly and we had a great chatting to Devada & Kadek agus, anya & chindy. Thank you!||One of the coolest hidden gems in Canggu, it's a tiny speakeasy bar that's absolutely worth discovering. I had a magical experience from start to finish, from finding the hidden key to unlock the door to perusing the creative menus and savoring the extraordinary drinks.

The place is beautifully designed, and the cocktails, like the Alice in Wonderland-inspired cocktail and the unique Babi Guling Negroni, are truly magical. With around 20 seats inside, it's an intimate space where every detail feels special, including the Alladin lamp inspired drink I ordered and the vampire-themed IV bag cocktail. Awesome experience!||Such an amazing place.
first time here and will definitely come back again.. and thank you to best bartender in town mr deva for explaining everything about the drinks on the menu.ğŸ»ğŸ»||What an absolute hidden gem!
Unbelievable bar and every single drink was so creative and tasted amazing.
The live music is spectacular
Special shout outs to the 2 Maestro Bartenders that served us Devada & Kadek. You too made it a very memorable night.
Also special shout outs to Big Boss No 1 Nuadi & Big Boss No 2 Wayan & Cindy. You were all amazing.
What a fun, amazing little place!
Will be back 10/10||Amazing little spot. A little tough to see where the entrance is when itâ€™s dark but the door guy helped us find it easily enough.

The vibes inside were great, they had a dj playing some good music

The cocktails were very good and creative.

But the thing that really made this place exceptional was the service, especially the manager (Gday?). He was helpful, friendly, making excellent conversation.

Would absolutely go again||A unique experience in Canggu, the bar's hidden beneath the mailbox room in which you have to search for the correct key to open the door. The place has this amazing vibe & ambience filled with laughter, the staff are very friendly and welcoming. I tried one of the cocktails called Lord of Himself, a whiskey based smoky cocktail, totally recommended!||Great design, i had only one negroni from their menu, that was very good, with a smoky flavor. Only down was the bill, where they add a weird 15% tax, + 7% tips and rounds the final number. I checked online to understand 15% taxâ€¦ non sense. For a 210k price, i ended up paying 290.||a well-known spot with a standout cocktail menuâ€”and honestly? they lived up to the hype. creative, well-crafted drinks and a super unique experience all around||Great little speak easy with a wide range of cocktails. Came in and the atmosphere was great with the 20s feel and music, this was spoilt later when a dj came in playing trashy club music. Needs to make up it's mine, either a 20s high class venue or a club, can't be both.||must visit speakeasy bar in berawa love the ambiance and Deva! great services! highly recommend to try! should make reservation first!||Amazing place, Deva and Kadek really know how to make good cocktails.

Super experience.||I originally stopped by Mailroom just for a quick cocktail, but ended up spending the whole evening there. All thanks to the amazing hospitality of the bartender, Devada. His warm conversation made me feel instantly welcome, and the vibe of the place is just so cozy and inviting. The music was top-notch too. Not too loud, just the right mood for a chill night. A sweet little spot with great energy.||Speakeasy cocktail bar! Need i say more. Showy drinks with presentations that lure you. Staffs that fancy a chat. Though the drinks still taste slightly layered with the flavours of each drink more completely amalgamated. Cool experience overall.

description_filled: An open-air complex offering diverse shopping, dining, and leisure, with a wide array of Asian and international cuisines. Features a vibrant evening atmosphere with live performances. Affordable and popular with tourists.
reviews_list:
['Really nice for an evening stroll, but with prices at least double the usual Nusa Dua prices. This goes for clothes, restaurants and spa too.
Very clean and well kept, perfect to get drinks with live music.'
 "Very touristy and can be three to five times more expensive in terms of cost of curios. Nearby star properties run shuttle services for their guests to go here. If you're looking for a bargain this isn't the right place. Maybe it was the off season but the whole store region was very dull and lacking vibrancy. Staff are otherwise helpful and there are a lot of local products here."
 'Bali Collection is a convenient place to shop if youâ€™re looking for souvenirs, clothes, or small gifts to bring home. The area is clean, safe, and well-organized, with a good variety of shops and restaurants all in one spot. Itâ€™s comfortable to walk around, and you donâ€™t have to deal with the heat or crowded street markets.

That being said, the shops are mostly tailored for tourists, so prices tend to be higher than what youâ€™d find in local markets, and many items feel quite similar from one store to another. If youâ€™re short on time and prefer the convenience of browsing in a relaxed environment, this place works well. However, for a more authentic and budget-friendly shopping experience, exploring local markets outside would give you more variety and better bargains.'
 "Not the most exciting shopping area, but it is clean and well maintained. The set up feels more like a park, which is actually quite nice. It is an outside shopping area with international brands like Quicksilver and Hard Rock Shop. The restaurants are more high end (affordable compared to European prices, but we're in Bali). Parking costs IDR 5000 per motorbike.

There's a free shuttle service in-between Hard Rock Shop and the Hard Rock Cafe in Kuta."
 'They have a lot of shops and restaurant, the place is quite nice not too crowded, also flea market. The toilet is also clean you can at night more convinience'
 "Unfortunately, it has lost it's charm. Back then it is great spot to look around and bought goodies. Nowadays it's like ghost town. There are some tourists walking here and there but the vibe is bland. Shop mostly deserted. The big one, Sogo, doesn't have new collection. Restaurants are too expensive. Plus side it is clean. Parking: car 10k and bike 5k"
 'Good selection of Shops and restaurants in convenient distance to Baliâ€™s 5 star resort area Nusa Dua.
A bit touristic with slightly higher prices but still cheaper than in the hotel resorts.'
 'We walked around as a family of 4 travelling from. AUSTRALIA. This is our 2nd visit here, we mostly enjoyed strolling around. The shops and restaurants appear quite expensive and on the higher end of pricing scale compared to elsewhere. I am aware that Nusa Dua is more luxurious than other places around Bali, however simple souvenirs and other items are at least 3 times the price.'
 'Nice shopping centre, Sogo
So many local soveneer
Take family walk around many shops restaurant ice cream

Great from family, especially with kids
No cars and clean..'
 'My visit to Bali Collection in Nusa Dua was a delightful blend of shopping, dining, and leisure in a serene and beautifully landscaped open-air complex. Set within the heart of Nusa Duaâ€™s resort area, this charming shopping village offers a mix of local handicrafts, international brands, boutique stores, and art galleries â€” perfect for picking up souvenirs or enjoying a relaxed stroll.

What truly enhanced the experience was the variety of dining options, ranging from cozy cafÃ©s to upscale restaurants. I enjoyed a pleasant meal surrounded by a tropical ambiance and warm Balinese hospitality. The atmosphere is calm and family-friendly, making it an ideal spot to unwind after a day at the beach or sightseeing.

Clean, well-maintained walkways, vibrant cultural touches, and occasional live entertainment add to its appeal. Whether youâ€™re shopping for quality gifts or simply looking to enjoy a relaxed evening with good food, Bali Collection is definitely worth a visit.'
 'This outdoor shopping mall is great with so many shops and restaurants. You will find just about everything. Great vibes at night as well.'
 'Bali Collection is a great place for shopping, dining, and relaxing in Nusa Dua. It has a wide variety of shops from local boutiques to international brands along with plenty of restaurants and cafes to suit any taste. The atmosphere is clean, safe, and family friendly, with a nice mix of modern comforts and Balinese charm. A perfect spot to spend a few hours enjoying food, shopping, or just strolling around.'
 "It's in the gated area of Nusa Dua so is dearer than outside.
All designer labels"
 'This is not a traditional local shopping center; it clearly feels designed for tourists, with prices higher than the local average. Walking through it, I honestly felt more like I was in an American mall than experiencing authentic local shopping. It looks very new to be fair.'
 'A decent place to shop, eat, hang out and chill especially in the Nusa dua side of Bali.

You get a wide variety to shop and eat.

The prices are tad on the higher side but considering the experience and the convenience of everything under one roof, guess itâ€™s ok.

The night time is lit up with lights

 'Bali Collection is a shopping arcade located in the prestigious hotels area in Nusa Dua, Bali. Here we can find many shops, restaurants and souvenir shops. name: Ayani Megamal
description: A popular downtown mall featuring fashion, a food court, and convenience stores. With a cinema on the top floor, it's an ideal spot for leisure and entertainment.
brief_description: Popular mall for fashion, dining, cinema, and convenience.
review_entities:
A convenience mall in the pontianak city center. Not too big but enough for me to hang out with family while trying various culinary among the tenants..I suggest you not to come late in sat day nite if you don't wanna lose the parking lot.||Used to come here a lot to hang out back in the days and still looked pretty much the same. Feeling a bit nostalgic when visiting this mall again. Definitely has pretty huge range of food selections, shops for shopping and miscellaneous.||Largest A yani mega mall in pontianak west kalimantan... good price shopping in hypermart  and other gallery ğŸ˜‰ â€¦||It's 1 of 2 malls in pontianak.  Clean, cool, has a hypermart.||I would give it 5 star if they change Matahari to Sogo or Metro and also put several mid up store such as charles and keith, pedro, staccato, aldo, Zara, Pull&Bear, Lacoste, H&M, Stradivarius, Bershka Cotton on (MAP brand). Add more F&B selection, the coffee bean, Burger king, Shaburi, Sushi tei, and pablo seems great. Closing amazone or funstation (one of them) so that can give many space. Fortunately, they have Starbucks, hush puppies, everbest, and rotelli which is hard to find in Kalimantan and only available in several mall in Indonesia. The parking lot such a hell. The toilets pretty clean. XXI is a lil bit old, they need to renovating it and adds IMAX and XXI premiere. On saturday, it feels like you were in traditional market because this is the only mall in town (I dont think the others is mall). Overall, it's average.||Ayani mega mall is the bigest mall in Pontianak. But actually it is just a small shopping mall. In the ground level, there a cafes and restaurants, clothes shop, bags shop and a supermarket 'hypermart', at fl1st and 2nd level there a matahari departement store, houseware, restaurant. There a gramedia book store at 1st level too. And food court located at the 2nd floor. At 3rd floor, there a cinema XXI and planet fit gym. So, it is a quite good and complete shopping mall,  but it is to pity that no an international brands such uniqlo and H&M store there, since most clothes I used are those brands.
At Sunday morning, they have a car free day event.||Nice place. Definitely must visit if you ever come to pontianak, you'll not be disappointedğŸ‘ğŸ» â€¦||One  biggest mall in pontianak, great place to hang out with family or friends, they got XXI theater and complete shop for clothing||toilet service is so bad lol||The first time I came to Kalimantan, I went to this mall, as I usually do when visiting a mall for the first time, just to watch a movie at the cinema. This cinema was the first and only one I had seen before, as the other cinema (which could be considered temporarily closed) was due to mall collapse. I wondered, â€œDo all residents who want entertainment have to go to this mall?â€ Especially if there are interesting movies that also happen to be available in neighboring countries, which can be reached via a more convenient land route.

Although this mall does not have a ground floor like most malls in other cities on Java Island, the tenants also support local SMEs by selling one of their signature products. Like most other malls, this one also has tenants in the F&B, lifestyle, hobby, electronics, and daily necessities sectors. Aming Coffee, a legendary coffee shop from the 1970s, was one of the tenants worth trying.

Although not all tenants have been experienced yet, especially those with the city's signature coffee flavor, I have had the opportunity to experience several other F&B tenants; such as Bakso Lapangan Tembak Senayan, a food court featuring Soto Medan with its tantalizing coconut milk aroma, CW Coffee with its original Arenga Sekar Asri blend, which has a strong palm sugar aroma and a bold taste on the tongue, Gramedia, and Hypermart. One memorable aspect of watching a movie here was getting a promo where you only pay the admin fee, which you can also get from a friend in one of the groups. My first movie watched here was GJLS: Ibuku Ibu Ibu, one of the most absurd films Iâ€™ve ever seen, possibly without any shortcuts or sharper editing. Everything felt authentic during filming, with a process filled with humor, as the three main characters were inherently funny and absurd.

From this, I learned that not every area necessarily has good access to accommodate all residents, especially in areas with high income or state revenue (wkwk), such as public transportation on the island of Java. Although access to this mall from my boarding house or workplace can be considered close, as it is within walking distance, it requires more effort to get there, especially after watching a night movie at the cinema. However, in my personal opinion, this serves as a lesson for the future, enabling me to own a private vehicle and drive it without fear. Fortunately, this area still has access to online-based transportation services like online ride-hailing apps, and it also supports online food ordering, which I previously thought was less accesible to many people.||Still the greatest shopping experience in Pontianak after all these years. Seems like has been upgraded since the last time I was here. Supermarket, departmental store, cineplex, hardware store, and eateries galore.||I think this is the biggest mall in Pontianak. Filled with many variant of tenants. But donâ€™t expect for â€œbrandedâ€ fashion in here. For food, it serve japanese, indonesian, western, and many more. The price of the foods also kinda affordable so dont worry. Also, it always hold some food festival in some period. For example, the last festival is Durian Festival to celebrate HUT Kota Pontianak Ke 248. Overall, it is recommended place to go if you are at Pontianak.||It's good mall with many shops and good food court.||Best & biggest mall in the city. Since 2004, it's become the one and only pleasure place for every single citizen who want to enjoy the market||The foodcourt is recommended. The cleaning service officers are responsive. Various kinds of culinary. Air-conditioned and smoking area are separated||The only decent shopping mall in Pontianak, not really much of an entertainment though, especially on weekends and holidays where it will be so crowded..||Still the best mall for exhibition or running a campaign despite the existence of few other bigger and modern malls in Pontianak.||First, it just typical mall that u can find anywhere in your country. No difference from our own mall. Try bakso here. I give 3 star because expensive & small potion. That's all I can say. ğŸ˜Œ â€¦||A nice place to escape to when Pontianak traffic overwhelms you.||A good mall with various stores and resto. It was quite crowded now (Nov 2020). The restorants in this mall still apply the physical distancing policy.

name: Shangri-La Jakarta
description: A highly-rated five-star hotel celebrated for its exquisite dining and attentive service. Rooms are comfortable with excellent amenities, featuring a lovely pool and garden. Satoo's diverse food and cake shop discounts are highlights.
brief_description: Top five-star hotel: superb dining, excellent service, comfortable rooms.
review_entities:
Staff serves with humility and care. Fantastic supeer food whole enchilada and tasty. Room super. Easy to work with.

Love the most the 50% off after 1700 at Satoo Cake Corner Lobby. Worth it yo.||I am SOOO impressed with the service of this hotel especially Kartini at the Satoo Restaurant. Sheâ€™s friendly, gave a lot of recommendations and made not just a small talk but real conversations. I will definitely come back.

Wanted to give thanks as well to the staff at the Horizon Club Lounge who had been super helpful!

Iâ€™ve been to quite a lot of hotels already. I can say that this hotel by far has the BEST SERVICE. Indonesian Hospitality at its finest.

Thank you and see you soon!!||Excellent service, I did not bring shoes to the gym and they provide me shoes to be used. Tennis court available for booking free of charge with tennis rackets only Rp. 46k for each for an hour. They have not only jacuzzi pool but also cold pool that is good for muscles recovery. Everything else facilities can be seen from the images uploaded. Unfortunately I did not take a single photo when having a breakfast. The restaurant has japanese food section, chinese food section, mie ayam sections, egg stations, fruit section, salads section, bread sections, middle east and indian sections, cheese stations and drinks station with variations of fruit juice and water.||From the moment we arrived, the service was outstanding. We booked extra tent, requested a birthday celebration, and were upgraded to the Horizon Club. Everything was perfect! Special thanks to Mas Arrayan and Mba Charlotte who assisted us and were very welcoming to our children. Thank you, Shangri-La Jakarta, we will definitely come back!||This is my 4th stay in Shangrila and here is my feedback:

1.The mattress is hard, hence my family quality of sleep is not memorable. In â€¦||Staying at Shangri-La Jakarta was truly amazing. My wife, 2 kids and I stayed here for 3 beautiful nights. The guest relations team of Komang, Emily, Andita, Nazwa, Syfa, Elisa & Halesya were very welcoming and checked on us via WhatsApp on a daily basis to see if we needed anything at all. They even offered to help us carry our bags on the day we arrived and book us restaurants for our meals and even theme park and indoor playground tickets. We actually planned this surprise trip to celebrate my sonâ€™s belated birthday and the guest relations team and Shangri-La Jakarta surprised us with nice birthday decorations in the room and an awesome birthday cake as well.

The buffet breakfast spread was phenomenal. They had a wide range of breakfast and food selection from the local Indonesian cuisine, to Chinese cuisine, Japanese cuisine, Indian cuisine, continental cuisine and their exceptional array of pastries and bakery items which we were all spoilt for choices. The almond croissant was super delicious as well as the Indian cuisine. The SATOO restaurant team of Kartini, Benny and Robby were super friendly and ensured we had everything taken care of for breakfast.

The room really nice, cozy and comfy and the swimming pool was super lovely and my kids loved the kids swimming area as well.

Thank you Shangri-La Jakarta for the wonderful hospitality and experience and the lovely stay! We will be sure to visit again in the near future!||The stay was amazing, me and my parents did enjoy the stay in shangri-la. Also, a big shoutout to the amazing Horizon Team for their thoughtfulness â€” Jennifer, Annisa, Bang Lurus, Pak Ronal, arrayan, Bang Sugi, Bang Robert, Fesya, Pak Eko, Bang Hendra, Fadzli, and Pak Abdul â€” for making our nights extra fun with those personalized touches!

Kudos to Ci Jenny, Geoffrey, Rena, Pak Bowo, and Pak Yanuar from Housekeeping for taking such great care of us, especially during the hectic moments â€” we truly appreciate it!

And of course, a huge thank you to everyone else behind the scenes who helped make our stay so memorable!||Stayed at Shangri-la Jakarta for a business trip and was blown away by the warm hospitality from the team, as well as amenities provided.

The daily breakfast crew made my mornings feel like a home away from home, especially Emi and Ismi who surprised me with a fruit platter one day! Special mention to Emi who was extremely warm & welcoming, and remembered my drink preferences.

Gym facilities were splendid and well maintained. Jacuzzi and steam room were a nice touch. Also opted for a massage at Chi spa and my masseuse, Ms Hana, was superb - my shoulder knots melted away.

All in all a great stay.||I had the privilege of hosting the PITO-JE2S 2025 medical conference at Shangri-La Hotel Jakarta, and the experience was truly outstanding. The facilities were world-class, the ambiance professional and welcoming, and the support from the â€¦||The best luxury experience ever.

Shangri-La Jakarta has taken care of its branding so well. I believe they must have trained all the staff with dignity and compassion to represent the brand before they commit to their work. I salute everyone who is well-mannered, professional, patient, gentle, entertaining, and accommodating toward all the guests. This is all part of one complete package. Thatâ€™s how we felt when we first arrived at the hotel.

Firstly, what we liked the most was the safety of the hotel. From the security checkpoint with the police dog to the check-in point for incoming cars, the hotel entrance, and the checkpoint leading to the hotel lobby, we felt very secure.

The greetings from the hotel staff when you get out of the car, along with their automatic assistance with your luggage, are top-notch. I canâ€™t mention everyone by name, but I appreciate each one of you. You guys are amazing.

Breakfast: The best breakfast buffet ever. The menu is very high-end. The chefs are exceptional, and the taste is beyond words. There is a wide variety of food. Once again, the staff are all so kind, always attending to us and checking on us, especially with my kids. Special mention to Kartini, Benny, and Robby. Thank you, guys. Both of my kids are in love with the donuts you served. The pastries are my top favoriteâ€”â€œAlmond Croissantâ€ is the best of the best. I already miss the taste.

Swimming Pool: The pool is so clean and relaxing, but what we liked most was the kidsâ€™ water playground, as my kids loved it so much. We could relax by the bar while watching our kids play in the water. Thatâ€™s the best concept.

Hotel Room: Thanks to the special staff who put in so much effort to decorate our room and surprise my son, who was celebrating his birthday at Shangri-La Jakarta. Special mention to Komang, Emily, Andita, Nazwa, Syfa, Elisa, and Halesya. Thank you, guys. Youâ€™re the best!

We will definitely come back again to Shangri-La Jakarta soon, as we felt so much at home, far away from home. Kudos to all the dedicated staff at Shangri-La Jakarta. Thank you all so much once again. ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ğŸ‘||A good service given by staff Ghaza when he delivered our meal to the room. Such a cheerful, polite staff with good communication skill. He even poured the soup for my colleague's sup buntut and gave us a plate of cut fruits.||Our favorite kids friendly hotel in Jakarta. The details to make the kids (and adults) feels at home is exceptional. The tent in the room, welcome kit for kids, the personal service level via WhatsApp and the daily extensive breakfast buffet. All in all a hotel we come back to every time we visit Jakarta.||Staff here and service here is beyond expectations. I had a driver pick me up at the baggage claim entrance. At the hotel, check in was less than 5 minutes. In my room, turnover service was already complete and I was met with welcome letters, a fruit basket, and dessert.

I surprised myself, not knowing how spacious and amazing the room was. The balcony was incredible.

The furniture in the room was a bit outdated, yet still felt high end. The rug was dirty and needed a severe deep cleaning. I saw many stains and always wore the provided slippers.

Room service was 5 stars for taste and time from order to delivery.

I had a in room massage by a woman named Tree. She was very professional and did amazing! My massage was first thing in the morning and I didn't want to leave afterwards, lol!

The hotel was not in a good area for walking. I took taxis when I wanted to leave. On the flip side it is very accessible by car and easy for visitors to come see you.

I had no serious issues here and really enjoyed my stay.||We stayed 2 nights in the Horizon Club room. Excellent  customer service, attentive to guests needs, quality toiletry items, comfortable room,  enjoyable club lounge experience with tasty food, options, drinks, and friendly staff. Good fitness centre. Nice big garden with extensive pool.||Stayed with my husband for a short trip on the 8 to 12 of august. Shangri La is always our second home in Jakarta. Thank you so much for Tsani from Sales Department. He always make sure that we will get the room that we want and also he â€¦||Shangri-La Hotel is very comfortable and the best choice for families and family events.|We celebrated our motherâ€™s birthday here and were assisted by the wonderful staff, especially Josephine. She gave us more than what we expected, â€¦||I love it here! Iâ€™m super picky and I love kind people and clean spaces. If you do too, this may be the place for you to stay ğŸ˜ƒ the food is good too! Even the late night room service menu! Rizki was very nice and professional!||I stayed at Shangri-La Jakarta during a recent business trip and it exceeded expectations. The hotel is perfectly located in the heart of the city, making it very convenient for meetings around Sudirman and the business district. My room â€¦||"I would like to express my deepest appreciation to one of the restaurant staff during breakfast, Ismi. From the moment we arrived, she welcomed us with a warm and pleasant smile. Her friendly attitude, calmness, and sincerity in ensuring our comfort were truly appreciated. Ismi was very attentive â€” giving food suggestions and politely checking in to see if we needed anything throughout our meal. Itâ€™s rare to find a staff member who is genuinely dedicated like her. Ismi truly brightened our morning and added value to our overall hotel experience. Thank you, Ismi, for your exceptional service. You are a valuable asset to the hotel team!"
The restaurant environment was also very attractive and comfortable, with a clean and well-organized setting that made our dining experience more enjoyable. The variety of food offered was excellent, with many delicious options to choose from.  With such pleasant surroundings and the warm service from staff like Ismi, our breakfast experience was truly memorable. Thank you, Ismi, for making our morning so special."

Once again, the staff are all so kind, always attending to us and checking on us, especially with my kids. Special mention to Kartini, Benny, and Robby. Thank you, guys. Both of my kids are in love with the donuts you served. The pastries are my top favoriteâ€”â€œAlmond Croissantâ€ is the best of the best. I already miss the taste.

Swimming Pool: The pool is so clean and relaxing, but what we liked most was the kidsâ€™ water playground, as my kids loved it so much. We could relax by the bar while watching our kids play in the water. Thatâ€™s the best concept.

Hotel Room: Thanks to the special staff who put in so much effort to decorate our room and surprise my son, who was celebrating his birthday at Shangri-La Jakarta. Special mention to Komang, Emily, Andita, Nazwa, Syfa, Elisa, and Halesya. Thank you, guys. Youâ€™re the best!

We will definitely come back again to Shangri-La Jakarta soon, as we felt so much at home, far away from home. Kudos to all the dedicated staff at Shangri-La Jakarta. Thank you all so much once again. ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ğŸ‘'
 "A good service given by staff Ghaza when he delivered our meal to the room. Such a cheerful, polite staff with good communication skill. He even poured the soup for my colleague's sup buntut and gave us a plate of cut fruits."
 'Our favorite kids friendly hotel in Jakarta. The details to make the kids (and adults) feels at home is exceptional. The tent in the room, welcome kit for kids, the personal service level via WhatsApp and the daily extensive breakfast buffet. All in all a hotel we come back to every time we visit Jakarta.'
 "Staff here and service here is beyond expectations. I had a driver pick me up at the baggage claim entrance. At the hotel, check in was less than 5 minutes. In my room, turnover service was already complete and I was met with welcome letters, a fruit basket, and dessert.

I surprised myself, not knowing how spacious and amazing the room was. The balcony was incredible.

The furniture in the room was a bit outdated, yet still felt high end. The rug was dirty and needed a severe deep cleaning. I saw many stains and always wore the provided slippers.

Room service was 5 stars for taste and time from order to delivery.

I had a in room massage by a woman named Tree. She was very professional and did amazing! My massage was first thing in the morning and I didn't want to leave afterwards, lol!

The hotel was not in a good area for walking. I took taxis when I wanted to leave. On the flip side it is very accessible by car and easy for visitors to come see you.

I had no serious issues here and really enjoyed my stay."
 'We stayed 2 nights in the Horizon Club room. Excellent  customer service, attentive to guests needs, quality toiletry items, comfortable room,  enjoyable club lounge experience with tasty food, options, drinks, and friendly staff. Good fitness centre. Nice big garden with extensive pool.'
 'Stayed with my husband for a short trip on the 8 to 12 of august. Shangri La is always our second home in Jakarta. Thank you so much for Tsani from Sales Department. He always make sure that we will get the room that we want and also he â€¦'
 'Shangri-La Hotel is very comfortable and the best choice for families and family events.|We celebrated our motherâ€™s birthday here and were assisted by the wonderful staff, especially Josephine. She gave us more than what we expected, â€¦'
 'I love it here! Iâ€™m super picky and I love kind people and clean spaces. If you do too, this may be the place for you to stay ğŸ˜ƒ the food is good too! Even the late night room service menu! Rizki was very nice and professional!'
 'I stayed at Shangri-La Jakarta during a recent business trip and it exceeded expectations. The hotel is perfectly located in the heart of the city, making it very convenient for meetings around Sudirman and the business district. My room â€¦'
 '"I would like to express my deepest appreciation to one of the restaurant staff during breakfast, Ismi. From the moment we arrived, she welcomed us with a warm and pleasant smile. Her friendly attitude, calmness, and sincerity in ensuring our comfort were truly appreciated. Ismi was very attentive â€” giving food suggestions and politely checking in to see if we needed anything throughout our meal. Itâ€™s rare to find a staff member who is genuinely dedicated like her. Ismi truly brightened our morning and added value to our overall hotel experience. Thank you, Ismi, for your exceptional service. You are a valuable asset to the hotel team!"
The restaurant environment was also very attractive and comfortable, with a clean and well-organized setting that made our dining experience more enjoyable. The variety of food offered was excellent, with many delicious options to choose from.  With such pleasant surroundings and the warm service from staff like Ismi, our breakfast experience was truly memorable. Thank you, Ismi, for making our morning so special."']

name: Bakso Mas Kumis
description: A beloved local spot for legendary meatballs, boasting an exquisite broth and perfectly chewy beef balls. Consistently crowded, it offers authentic flavors at affordable prices, making it a must-try destination.
brief_description: Legendary meatballs with delicious broth, chewy, popular, affordable.
review_entities:
Too pricey, the last  customer with no discount, no veggies, meatball taste ordinary, the portion was not worthed
Many places are better, they event not as good as expensive meatball like A fung.||Best bakso in town.

Meaty and tasty ğŸ‘Œ
Located around Djarum area so some people call it bakso djarum..

Bcareful when putting sambal to your bowl. The sambal very hot.||Cheap and delicious. You know you are in for something good when you are trying a new place, and there is a line to get in. The place is fairly famous,  believe me word has gotten out about how good this place is. Have a seat and grab some crackers ( I became addicted to the smaller breadstick looking ines) out of the big plastic tub in front of you. The meatball soup isnt life changing but it IS very good at an exceptionally good deal. For 2 people with crackers and drinks it was less than 100k. Awesome.||The best place for lunch if you are baso addicted||one of the best bakso i taste in jakarta so far. their meatballs is very meaty. you can ask for their 'tetelan', it's more like meat with a bit fat, but taste good.||They serve amazing bakso (meatball dish) with vermicilli noodle put into it, you can really taste the beef, unlike some other place where you can barely taste it. There're no gorengan (fried fritters) to put into though, but it's still delicious even without it.

Place's super crowded during the day, would recommend to visit during the evening instead.||One of the best bakso ( beef meatball ) in Jakarta, the meatball is very delicious, they served with rice vermicelly and a few beef meat that already cut small size. The place is clean and the serving is fast.||Bakso was delicious no doubt. Too bad it doesn't have other branch outside this one||One of best Bakso in Jakarta. The soup is clear but thick. So refreshing for tired soul. Hahaha. They have option for your carbo needs, rice, noodle, or rice vermicelli. You can add your pleasure with Ice Cream Durian in near of Bakso Mas Kumis.||Clean but a little bit hot. Service galak, but good quality of bakso.||If you came to Jakarta Indonesia, one of the must try Bakso/Meatballs Restaurant. Wow this is another level of Bakso Dish. Two thumbs up. Indonesia have a different kind of bakso depending on the area. This resto have a Solo Bakso variation . From the broth, the depth of broth is on another level really love it, the meatball itself only have one kind, crunchy and chewy, love love the consistency and the meat is fresh homemade, and they gave you beef meat too. If you like spice the sambal is another level, realy spicy. If you can't handle spice, 1/2 of teaspoon is enough so watch out, the crispy fried spring onion also bring this Bakso to perfection. The only downside if there is no fresh lime to add sour to your dish but they serve cuka/vinegar. The atmosphere is really crowded, almost every time for brunch/or lunch. So you must efficient or a little fast to finish your dish, but everything is worthed. The Bakso Mas Kumis Slipi Dish is so delicious. Give it a try||The meatballs are delicious, for lunch hours you have to queue for a while, but the table turnover is quite fast so you don't have to queue for a long time.||One of my favorite place when carve for Bakso (Indonesian Meatballs).  The meatballs itself are very good because it is freshly made from ground beef and it is very chewy and the broth taste is superb too (very beefy broth).  Since it's meatballs from Surakarta / Solo I expect they serve several kinds of meatballs ( Egg meatball, cheese meatball. beef ribs and etc.  Note:  If  you want to visit this place during  lunch time especially in weekdays it will be very crowded and it is very difficult to find the parking spot.||uhmmm well to be honestâ€¦.. it does taste good but for 40k i dont know.||Best bakso in jakarta so far. The broth is thick and flavorful but the price is affordable. This reminds me bakso place i ate in solo. You get 4 bakso and some meat (not the fat but real meat). This place only sell bakso, but you can choose to add noodle or not.||bakso was so good, so authentic. so far the best bakso in town and the sambal is to die for. please provide more chairs and table for the crowd!!||Lo and behold all of you bakso purist out there who said," heh? Kok makan bakso pake nasi!?". Majority who came here (when I visited) ordered that; bakso and nasi! And it put them on the trending train enough to create FOMO.

3 stars food just because the bakso is so average. I don't know about you guys, but, I know places that offers the same level of delicacy with half of the price. Oh, it's 38k per portion by the way.

2 stars service, during my visited I kept hearing," mas tadi saya pesen X tapi belum keluar". With a price range offered, yeah, 2 stars. Oh, the thing that make me sewot the most there were no price sign, the last place I visited that doesn't have such thing was puncak where in the end i have to pay 100rb for an Indomie, a cup of coffee, and a pack of cigarettes back then pre 2000. It's feels almost like a tourist bait.

4 stars atmosphere, now this is where it excel. IMHO, this place offer the minimum requirements for people who are willing to pay 38k per portion for Bakso Kampung. You'll meet with well-groomed-foreign-raised tionghoa descendants, member for Elektra glide riders, down to emak2 who drove Ignis. There were sign," dilarang bungkus sambal" and "dilarang bawa hewan peliharaan" all over the place, it spell enough the demographic.

Conclusion. Yeah, come here to check what's the hype all about. Bring your friends so you can say," Chuaks!" to them or to say," see it's packed even on Sunday 5pm". Or to destroy the dogma that bakso can't be eaten with nasi. Everything else? Pour moi, I rather have a 15k a bowl of bakso near by than to drive 30-40 minutes there.

Hint: if you really really on the mood of adventure trying out an extraordinary bakso, go to Bakso Son Haji Sonny at Condet. IMHO it's offered something unusual (bakso with a hint of middle east)||So gewddsss ğŸ˜‹ probably best bakso in Jakarta||Eat meatballs close to Djarum, which is one of the legendary meatballs in West Jakarta. The taste of the meatball soup doesn't have much flavour, the taste of the meat is strong, shredded meat is served in the dish, and a pot of chili sauce is available on the table, if you want to add more.||I am a fan of meat, and bakso is one of my fav dish. Bakso means meatball, and bakso djarum is the best bakso in jakarta. The sambal is very very cery spicy. So watch it. This restaurant is always crowded, especially on lunch. Dont forget to try this one!

brief_description: Popular eatery, delicious dishes, cozy atmosphere, affordable prices.

Mie hotpan nya cuma kerasa pedes, gk ada sedep gurihnya. Kayak ada yg kurang. Kebab jawa pedas patty nya kurang mateng, lemon tea gk berasa lemonnya sama aja seperti es teh biasa.

Pelayanan oke aja, tapi kasirnya salah nulis pesenan. Harusnya pesen 2 porsi cuma ditulis satu.

Bisa dibilang, tempat ini adalah salah satu tempat makan yang sangat murah yang ada di Sidoarjo. Tempatnya terletak di dekat Alun-alun Sidoarjo dan cukup strategis karena berada di tengah kota Sidoarjo.

Harga makanan di sini juga sangat murah, namun sayangnya masih belum ada menu berupa nasi. Hanya ada beberapa pilihan makanan seperti Mie Lumer, Burger, Kebab, dan juga ada pilihan2 menu atau minuman lain. Untuk rasanya sendiri sudah terbilang enak dengan harga yang murah, Mie Lumer hanya dibanderol sekitar 10-13k tergantung level pedas yang dipilih.

Minumannya juga terbilang murah, ada pilihan Mojito, Latte, dan varian Teh. Saya mencoba varian Strawberry Latte dan surprisingly rasanya enak. Tempat ini recommended banget buat yang mau cari tempat nongki di tengah kota Sidoarjo.

Steak menu ranges from around 100k.

Here I choose potato waffle and mashed potatoes, the steak is cooked medium with garlic butter. The BBQ sauce are there because they gave us the option. The steak are already good on it's own honestly and doesn't need any sauce. In the menu it said that the porterhouse is for 2-3 person. 10/10 would order the menu again.

Prices were cheaper than competitors that we used to dine in, but great value which comes with great taste.

name: Pempek Ci' Awa
description: A popular Palembang specialty snack shop, celebrated for its signature fresh fish pempek, savory tekwan soup, and grilled squid. Offers authentic flavors at budget-friendly prices.
brief_description: Authentic Palembang snacks, great taste, budget-friendly prices.
review_entities:
Kesini dari Depok, sengaja cari mpek-mpek. Untuk rasa mpek-mpek nya yang enak itu jenis adaan dan kapal selam nya, lembut dan berasa banget ikannya. Sementara jenis lainnya kurang memuaskan. Rasa ikan dan kelembutannya di bawah adaan dan kapal selamnya. Buat jenis kulit, entah apa yang salah dari adonanya yang jelas buat lidah aku enggak memuaskan, ada rasa gosong dan gak kurang rasa. Buat cuka nya standar rasa cuko kebanyak, gak ada rasa istimewa yang bikin balik. Harga mpek-mpek nya mulai dari 5 RB untuk yang kecil sampai 18 RB untuk yang besar.

Minumnya baik teh atau es jeruk kurang manis. Malah ada satu gelas yang gak manis sama sekali.

Sementara seafood nya, oke ya ... Gak ada bau amis berlebihan, matengnya pas jadi gak Alot. Saus bakarnya juga meresap sampai ke dalam terutamaenu ayam koreanya. Cocok banget di cocol pake saus Padang yang weeenak ... Mpek-mpek juga cocok pake saus ini. Harga menu seafoodnya 35 RB per tusuk nya, begitu juga dengan kerangnya. Tersedia nasi juga ya disini. Pertusuk satenya besar, jadi bisa buat di makan berdua.

Oke deh, selamat mencoba ...
Semangat dan sukses buat sate cumi dan mpek-mpek ci Awa. Semoga pelayanan, dan rasa makanannya makin enak. â˜…â˜…â˜…â˜…â˜… Delicious French sandwich in Bidadari !

Just discovered this gem on Jalan Bidadari and I'm so glad we did! The French Burger offers a wonderful taste of France right here in Bali. My friend and I ordered takeaway and tried their traditional jambon beurre and jambon emmental - both were absolutely delicious and authentically prepared. The bread was fresh and perfectly crusty, and the fillings were generous and flavorful.
Their homemade French fries were a standout - crispy on the outside, fluffy inside, just like you'd find in a good Parisian bistro. The menu has great variety with burgers, baguette sandwiches, cold sandwiches, and croques, so there's something for everyone.
What really made the experience special was meeting the owners - a lovely Indo-French couple who are incredibly friendly and welcoming. You can tell they put real care into their food and service. While we took our order to go, the restaurant looked inviting with nice air conditioning for those hot Bali days.
The French Burger fills a real niche in the Kerobokan dining scene. If you're craving authentic French sandwich fare or just want to try something different from the usual Bali options, this place is definitely worth a visit. We'll certainly be back to try more of their menu!

name: Boga Rasa Aneka Kue basah
description: A legendary wet cake shop popular for its wide selection of local and international pastries. Ideal for breakfast or snacks, it offers affordable prices and consistently draws crowds.
brief_description: Legendary wet cake shop: complete selection, affordable, always busy.
review_entities:
Lengkap disini segala macem kue.. minuman juga ada. Risoles mayo kudu cobain, sus dll nya juga lengkap. Hari senin libur||Tempatnya enak, kuenya lengkap buat sarapan, dan dekat dengan lapang jadi bisa sekalian olahraga :)||Tempat kue basah legend. Banyak pilihannya. Rasanya juga enak-enak semua.||Tempat baru pindah ke seberangnya (awalnya di lapangan). Dari jam 6 udah buka & libur tiap senin sih kalau pas ditempat sebelumnya. Selalu penuh sama ibu2, terus yg mau bekel ke sekolah atau kantor ğŸ˜
Banyak pilihan, dari mulai jajanan pasar sampe internasional juga ada. Kalo mau kesini mending aga pagian, kalo terlalu siang udah pada abis. Kalo terlalu pagi juga belum ngumpul semua kuenya.
Pokonya langganan ibuku disini. Bisa pesen buat acara2. Pernah anter ibu ambil pesenan jam 5an pagi. Tetehnya juga baik bgt||Variasi kue jajanannya cukup banyak ragamnya, rasa cukup enak.||Mantap banyak pilihan kuenya dan harganya murah||Jajan pasar mantap di Margahayu Raya||Banyak pilihan dan murah. Cuma||Cari kue basah emng rekomendasi ke sini, dekat rumah pula..||Yummy||Hari ini (13/03/2025) sore saya dateng mengenakan atribut gojek. Berencana beli jajanan pasar utk takjil keluarga dirumah. Bukan kali pertama beli jajanan pasar disini. Saya di layani oleh Tante yg berkacamata dan ibu yg berkerudung. Saat memilih Tante yg berkacamata sangat responsif meski ngga bertatap muka, karena kebetulan sudah ramai pembeli. Sepertinya, ada 3-4 pengunjung yg sedang memilih dan membeli. Saat pembayaran, saya di layani oleh ibu yg berkerudung. Entah apa masalah ibu itu dengan saya, saya di layani dgn tidak menyenangkan. Padahal ibu bekerja di bidang pelayanan sama seperti saya. Saat itu saya hanya meminta di packing lebih baik karena kebetulan rumah saya jauh dari warung kue basah ini dan cuaca menuju rumah saya sudah gelap yg saya takutkan akan terkena air hujan. Awalnya saya minta kresek lebih, kemudian saya minta ripet(jika ada). Saya minta juga ga maksa. Namun ibu itu bicara dengan nada yg kurang enak didengar didepan umum. Sengaja ngga saya balas lagi, karena saya ga suka ribut didepan umum. Kalo lagi capek/sedang ada masalah lebih baik izin tidak bekerja aja, karena ibu bekerja akan ketemu banyak pengunjung yg mgkn lebih banyak minta nya dari saya. Buat pemilik warung kue basah ini , jika membaca ulasan saya. Alangkah baiknya, ibu berkerudung itu ditempatkan di belakang dapur saja. Karena di khawatirkan ada yg baperan seperti saya. Bukankah pekerjaan di bidang jasa mengutamakan keramahan, pelayanan dan juga harus bisa jaga emosi hehe karena saya juga diajarkan seperti itu selama saya bekerja â˜ºï¸

name: Alfamart Pangkalan Asem 2
description: A convenient store offering daily necessities, snacks, and an ATM. Friendly service is noted, with added tire repair services available.
brief_description: Convenient store: daily goods, snacks, ATM, friendly service, tire repair.
review_entities:
Mantap||Belanja di sini pegawainya ga teliti, barang saya kurang 1 ga di masukin ke kantong belanja udah di bayar, sampai rumah di cek ga ada, mau balik lagi capek jalannya.ğŸ˜­ â€¦||.rv uj.||Pelayanannya ramah dan sabar||Pelayananya ramah dan baik||Belanja||Lokasi strategis dan lengkap||Saya senang bila berbelanjadi sna?||ramah pelayanannya dan tersedia tempat parkirnya||Good||mantap, karyawan y ramah terutama DIVA dan BUMIL, Mantap lah||Selalu kecewa belanja di alfa, ni saya berbicara fakta bukan mengada-ngada apalagi fitnah, gk sama sekali
Bulan lalu saya beli voucher detol alfamart di go dealsnya gojek app, udh dibeli pas mau dipake di alfamart ternyata komputer alfamart tsb error gk bisa di input di mesin pos kasir, gk tau ya apa bener gak bisa atau cuma ngada2 si kasirnya karena mungkin dia kasir baru dan gak ngerti cara pke voucher klo customer belanja, gk tau karena gak liat langsung di komputer nya, cuma kasirnya bilang gtu ya w percaya aja

Pas selang 2 hari gue mau ke alfamart lagi nukerin voucher, eh ternyata vouchernya udh hilang dan w baru tau di menu bantuan klo udh di swipe up vouchernya, voucher tsb akan hilang dalam waktu 2x 24 jam deh klo gk salah bacannya gtu

Nah dalam hal ini w yg dirugiin dong pastinya !!! Gue tuh beli loh voucher detol nya itu 15rb di go deals
Bukan voucher gratis
Berharap nya dapat potongan 30rb, tapi malah gue rugi 15rb
Sangat mengecewakan, udh w lapor pihak call centre alfamart tapi katanya w disurub lapornya ke call centre gojek
Gue udh email ke call centre gojek divisi go deals tapi gk di tanggapi sampe skrg
Udh berapa bulan berlalu dari w email ! :(
Parah banget2

Setiap ad promo jg barangnya selalu terbatas, emg gk direncanakan dlu klo mau promo berapa stoknya ?!
Seakan akan promo cuma tuk narik customer datang doang, tapi klo pas datang ternyata barangnya gk ada yang ada bukannya beli, malah kesel, kecew dan kapok belanja di alfamart
Mending belanja di Indomaret gk ada masalah :( !!!!

Dan tolong dong tuk pembayaran gopay, harusnya batasnya itu sampe jam setengah 10 atau jam 10 sesuai jam tutup toko
Orang mau belanja kok di persusah sih?
Situ bisnis cari untung atau cari rugi,  heran

Semoga ditanggapi oleh pihak alfamart, alfamidi dan alfa group ya
Udh banyak yg pada kecewa, bukan hanya saya aja
Tp mungkin cuma saya yg berani berkomentar, berani mengkritik
Saya termasuk bagian dari local guidenya google jadi ni fakta bukan ngada2 ! :(||Ada pungli di depan alfamart ini||Semangat mas gal||Ada layanan tambal ban/fast moving kendaraan...pake tukang parkir jgğŸ¤”, mainan banyak tp gak update... â€¦||has many choice of product, also has ATM, good for buying toiletries in a rush, also has selection for quick bite||Sangat membantu area sekitar||Lama dalam proses pesanan online
Kurang komunikasi
Barang banyak tak tersedia||Kasir diAlfamart Pangkalan Asem bener2 gajelas sumpah. Pelayanannya buruk bgt, kasinya mau cewek/cowok ga ramah, ga ada senyum atau eye contact kpd konsumennya, ada produk yg gratis setiap pembeliian apapun malah ga dikasih, sudah 2x saya begini, dan selalu lupa, selalu ingetnya pas udh drmh.

Tukang parkirnya juga ga jelas, mentang2 ibu2 tapi ga disebrangin, padahal dia ngeliat saya lagi kesusahan mau nyebrang, tapi dia juga diem aja, cuma mintain duit doang sambil main hp.

JANGAN BELANJA DIALFAMART CABANG SINI LAGI LAH.||Di Alfamart tersebut ada tukang parkir ibu-ibu. Sewaktu saya kesana ingin membeli barang tetapi  barang yang saya cari sedang kosong, ketika ingin naik motor ibu-ibu tersebut menagih uang parkir, karena saya tidak jadi berbelanja dan saya hanya membawa uang seratus ribu saya membayar parkir dengan uang seratus ribu tetapi ibu itu malah bilang saya tidak niat untuk mengasih.  Sebelumnya saya kesana selalu membayar parkir. Dan memang ibu tersebut hanya bisa duduk dan meminta uang tanpa mengatur parkir.

1. Dari beberapa makanan yg saya pesan, ga satu pun diberikan tissue. Di meja pun tidak ada. Mungkin mbanya lupa. Untung saya bawa sendiri.
2. Dear crew, ini kan sistemnya self service ya, please, kebersihan traynya diperhatikan. Itu kotor banget lho kemarin, banyak bercak minuman dan makanan. Gampang koq, tinggal dilap aja dengan towel basah sebelum meletakkan makanan di atas tray. Kan malu kalo kotor.
3. Dear mba mba crew, berhubung indoor cafe ini lumayan besar, masih tergolong baru jadi masih sedikit furniture, jadi suara kalian pelan pun akan terdengar. Tolong dijaga volume suaranya. Dan hindari berkerumun. Jika kalian menjadi Cstmer pasti juga ga akan nyaman. Jangan lupa, cstmer akan kembali bukan hanya krna makanan, tapi juga kenyamanan.
4. Crewnya perlu ditraining lagi ya cara berkomunikasi dgn cstmer. Ada salah satu crew yg menurut saya bahasa dan gesturnya agak kurang. Mungkin krna masih baru.

Untuk toiletnya bersih, parkiran cukup untuk beberapa mobil dan makanannya acceptable. Lumayan enak..

Mungkin nanti saya akan kembali dan review ulang lagi jika cafenya sudah lebih rapi.

Terimakasih'
 'Tempat nya nyaman utk meeting dan pelayanan nya memuaskan..']

Mampir ke Point Cafe nya Karawitan guys buat beli minuman Monday Promonya. Begitu masuk, eh ternyata ada sedikit renovasi, dimana indoor areanya sudah dipasang meja kursi dan outdoor areanya juga ditambah meja panjang lurus gitu. Suka sih sama renovasinya, terutama indoor areanya dimana kita jadi bisa ngopi dengan fasilitas AC Indomaret dan terhindar dari Smoking Area.

 'It was fluppy'

 'Siplah'
 'Bersih, parkiran luas, rasa lumayan enak, d bawah ad toko daging jd biasa ny kl bli daging skalian makan d atas. Good concept ğŸ‘'
 'Tempat nyaman banget.\nAda mushola yg nyaman.\nTempat makan nyaman banget.\nMinus nya cuma toiletnya aja gerah banget, tapi bersih pol semuanyaaaa...\nTempat parkir luas dan nyaman, gratis jugaaa..\n\nMenu nya enak2 murah.'
 'Resto favorit keluarga. Tempatnya nyaman, dekat rumah, pelayanannya ramah, parkirnya luas.\n\nHarga steaknya terjangkau, tersedia mulai dari yang 50rb hingga 300rb. Follow sosial medianya untuk info promo. Rasa makanannya juga enak.\n\nSelain steak ada juga menu lainnya seperti sop iga, mie goreng, cumi goreng, tongseng dll.'
 'Baru ngeh ada kedai steak yang nyaman dan dekat rumah padahal kata staffnya mereka sudah hampir setahun disini. Lokasinya cukup strategis, parkirannya luas. Lantai bawah ada toko daging, frozen food dan groceries yang lumayan lengkap. Sedang lantai atasnya adalah kedai steaknya. Interiornya cukup cantik, bersih dan area makannya luas. Tersedia juga private room. Bisa pilih steaknya disajikan dengan hotplate atau piring biasa. Ada paket promo combo nya yg lumayan murah harganya. Dagingnya dibakar sesuai request, masih juicy dan cukup lembut. Kentangnya juga dimasak cukup enak, hanya mashed potatonya mungkin kalo lbh creamy akan lebih mantap. Sausnya yang perlu diimprove, terlalu asin bagi saya yg mushroom nya. But overall puas dan worthed it']
